{"title": "Grand Inquisitor Scene", "content": "In stories set in a dystopian society, there is usually the one scene in the story where a dissident of the society has a \"meeting of the minds\" with a high ranking official of the society. During the meeting, the official can perfectly understand where the dissident is coming from with his objections, but has a rebuttal for each one, and explains why his vision for the society are flawed and thus wouldn't work. In a Crapsack World setting, the official will state how they've stamped it out and such.\n\nUsually also serves as a Breaking Speech, as the dissident has their mind blown by how the authorities are so much smarter and more powerful than the dissident dreamed.\n\nThere are also cases where the official doesn't support the society, but explains how it works and why people think the way they think.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GrandInquisitorScene", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/BatmanHolyTerror", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/TheMatrix", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheMatrix", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheMatrixReloaded", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheMatrixRevolutions", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Equilibrium", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheBrothersKaramazov", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/NineteenEightyFour", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/BraveNewWorld", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheGiver", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Fahrenheit451", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Discworld", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/We", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/RayBradbury", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/HarlanEllison", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/SherlockHolmes", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/DarknessAtNoon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BlakesSeven", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheTwilightZone1959", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheXFiles", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Music/Rush", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/GeorgeBernardShaw", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Theatre/SaintJoan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Theatre